<HEADLINE>
USC LANDS ANOTHER OFFENSIVE LINEMAN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ USC received an oral commitment Sunday from
Newport Harbor High offensive lineman Blair Jones, considered one
of the top players at his position in the state.
</P>
<P>
   Jones (6-foot-7, 244 pounds) selected USC over Michigan,
Colorado and Washington. He is the 15th player to commit to the
Trojans, who have seven scholarships remaining.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans have received commitments from three offensive
lineman: Jones, Joe McGuire of Servite High and Phillip Eaves of
Riverside Community College.
</P>
<P>
   Another offensive lineman, Travis Watkins (6-4, 290) of Helix
High in San Diego, could commit to the Trojans this week. He has
narrowed his choices to USC and San Diego State.
</P>
<P>
   USC reserve defensive lineman Darren Collins, who will be a
senior next year, is transferring to a Division I-AA school.
Portland State is the front-runner.
</P>
</TEXT>
