   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SKI-LAKE-PLACID (Lake Placid, N.Y.) _ The streets have not
bustled with this much anticipation in 20 years, the natives of
this tiny Essex County village will tell you. Banners and signs
that welcome the world are as omnipresent on Main Street as the
icicles that hang off rooftops. Next month, the inaugural Winter
Goodwill Games begin here, the biggest on a list of big events that
have marked Lake Placid's reemergence on the international winter
sports scene. By TIM REYNOLDS.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NINERS (San Francisco) _ The pro football draft is the
subject of much interest hereabouts because the San Francisco 49ers
own the third pick overall. Whether they will use it is another
mattering altogether because of general manager Bill Walsh's
penchant for trading down to acquire more picks. By JOHN
CRUMPACKER.
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOORS-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ The biggest toy store ever
assembled opened its doors last Friday for a 10-day run, but hidden
away in the back are the real treasures. The toy store, in this
case, is the San Francisco Sports and Boat Show at the Cow Palace,
renovated this year with 1,000 new boats, hundreds of motors and
gear in eight halls, along with halls featuring adventure travel,
fishing and golf. By TOM STIENSTRA.
</P>
