<HEADER>
A8075 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u t BC-TRAVEL-GO-AUSTRALIA-H     01-17 0694
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-GO-AUSTRALIA-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHEN YOU GO: GREAT OCEAN ROAD 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ Getting there: Qantas Airways and United Airlines schedule
nonstop jet service between Los Angeles and Melbourne. Connections
are available via Sydney on those airlines and on Air New Zealand.
A travel agent can provide schedules and costs.
</P>
<P>
   Qantas offers sharp discounts on flights within Australia when
combined with an international ticket. Contact a travel agent for
details. Air New Zealand operates a similar program in conjunction
with Ansett Australia airlines.
</P>
<P>
   _ When to go: Australia's seasons are reversed from those in the
United States, but the climate is mild year-round along the Great
Ocean Road. Hotel accommodations are hard to acquire in December,
January and other holiday periods. Advance reservations are advised
for any weekend.
</P>
<P>
   _ Packages: Several companies can arrange packages that feature
the Great Ocean Road and Melbourne. Austravel, which has offices in
Houston, can handle lodging and rental car arrangements; call
800-633-3404 or 713-965-9141, or access www.austravel.net. Or
consult a travel agent about this and other packages.
</P>
<P>
   _ Lodging: We stayed at the Lorne Main Beach Motor Inn in Lorne
and the Southern Ocean Motor Inn in Port Campbell. Both are
affiliated with Australia's Flag Hotels chain, and arrangements
were made through Austravel. While not luxurious, the properties
were comfortable and well-maintained with costs less than $100 U.S.
for a double room. The Southern Ocean Motor Inn featured Port
Campbell's best restaurant; eateries and shops were only a short
walk from the Lorne Main Beach Motor Inn.
</P>
<P>
   Other lodgings are available en route, and a travel agent can
offer options.
</P>
<P>
   _ Documentation: A valid U.S. passport and an Australian visa
are required. But unlike in some countries, a visa costs nothing
and is easy to acquire. It's processed electronically, so you don't
have to carry a document. A travel agent or tour packager can
handle details. The visa is valid for up to three months in
Australia.
</P>
<P>
   _ Currency: The Australian dollar has been trading at about
$1.53 to $1 U.S.
</P>
<P>
   _ Clothing: Casual attire is appropriate throughout the region.
Evenings can become chilly; a sweater or light jacket is
recommended.
</P>
<P>
   _ Time: The state of Victoria is 15 hours ahead of Houston. If
it's 9 a.m. Sunday along the Great Ocean Road, it's 6 p.m. Saturday
in Houston.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
DETOURS:  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ Grampians National Park is situated only about a three-hour
drive north from the western extreme of the Great Ocean Road. This
413,000-acre mountainous park is rich in wildlife. Access
www.travelaustralia.com.au/vic/grampians on the Internet. &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; _ Ballarat, a one-hour drive northwest from Geelong, is a
historic gold-mining town. Access www.ballarat.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Olympics: A reminder to those who want to combine an excursion
along the Great Ocean Road and/or a stay in Melbourne with a visit
to Sydney during the 2000 Olympics. The Summer Games are scheduled
Sept. 15-Oct. 1 in Sydney. For information about remaining tickets
and packages, call Cartan Tours, the designated U.S. distributor,
at 800-841-1994; or access www.cartan.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
ADDITIONAL INFORMATION: &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ The Australian Tourist Commission is an excellent source for
information about the entire continent and maintains offices in the
United States. Call 800-369-6863 to speak with a travel counselor
or to request a vacation planning kit. Access www.australia.com on
the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tourism Victoria can provide brochures and maps covering the
Great Ocean Road, Melbourne and all of Victoria. Write to 55
Collins Street, Melbourne 3000, Victoria, Australia. Access
www.tourism.vic.gov.au.
</P>
<P>
   _ Contact Geelong Otway Tourism by writing to 17 Gheringhap St.,
Geelong 3220, Victoria, Australia. E-mail
got(at)greatoceanrd.org.au. Access www.greatoceanrd.org.au on the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
   _ Contact Shipwreck Coast Tourism by writing to P.O. Box 1467,
174A Timor Street, Warrnambool 3280, Victoria, Australia. E-mail
shpwrec(at)tpgi.com.au.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
