<HEADLINE>
PRISTINE BUSTER KEATON PRESERVES THE GENIUS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Art of Buster Keaton'' (DVD) _ Who can ever
tire of the genius of Buster Keaton? This marvelous set includes
most of the silent film star's great work, including ``The
General.'' The stone-faced comic is well served by the pristine
picture quality of the remastered titles. Kino on Video deserves
kudos for making these titles available, even though they're not a
box-office threat to James Bond or Austin Powers.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Extreme Adventures of Super Dave'' _ Super Dave Osborne,
played by Bob Einstein (Albert Brooks's brother), had a great run
as a comic version of Evel Knievel on his Showtime series. Einstein
knows how to use the variety-show format to poke fun at stuntmen
and show business. But the movies are another thing altogether. The
sense of spontaneity on the half-hour show _ though contrived _ did
give Super Dave a sense of immediacy. The movie's just a tired
replay as worn and tattered as one of Osborne's red, white, and
blue jumpsuits after a terrible accident.
</P>
<P>
   ``Animal Farm'' _ This adaptation of George Orwell's allegorical
tale of tyranny and oppression is miraculous. Director John
Stephenson skillfully blends live action and animatronics to create
a believable world. Like the book, there are some violent moments.
Ultra-sensitive parents might want to prescreen the movie.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Jan. 18: ``Bowfinger'' (DVD), ``An Ideal
Husband,'' ``Twin Falls Idaho'' (DVD), ``The Hitchhiker,'' ``From
Dusk to Dawn 3,'' ``Bonanno: A Godfather's Story,'' ``The 13th
Warrior,'' ``The Wood'' (DVD). Jan. 25: ``Runaway Bride''(DVD),
``My Life So Far,'' ``The Sex Monster,'' ``My Son the Fanatic,''
``Love Is in the Air,'' ``Conceiving Ada'' (DVD), ``The Tempest,''
``Woman Wanted.'' Feb. 1: ``Love Stinks'' (DVD), ``The Winslow
Boy'' (DVD), ``The Cabinet of Dr. Caligari,'' ``Nosferatu.'' Feb.
8: ``Blue Streak'' (DVD), ``Fist of the Legend,'' ``Romance,''
``Absence of the Good'' (DVD), ``Ruby Bridges.'' Feb. 15: ``Grey
Wolf,'' ``Breakfast of Champions,'' ``Mob Queen,'' ``Big Fella''
(DVD), ``Song of Freedom'' (DVD), ``In Too Deep,'' ``Daughters of
the Dust'' (DVD), ``Total Recall 2070,'' ``Entropy,'' ``Joe the
King'' (DVD), ``The Lovers on the Bridge.'' Feb. 22: ``Get
Bruce!,'' ``Bats,'' ``Tail Lights Fade'' (DVD), ``Galaxina,''
``Conspirators of Pleasure'' (DVD).'' Feb. 29: ``Stigmata'' (DVD),
``Random Hearts'' (DVD), ``The Suburbans'' (DVD), ``One Man's
Hero'' (DVD).
</P>
