<P>
   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IOWA-DEBATE (Des Moines) _ Al Gore and Bill Bradley talk about
race in their last Iowa debate. By Bob Hohler and Susan Milligan.
1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-CRIME (Boston) _ President Clinton visits Boston
Tuesday, stopping at Orchard Gardens Community Center in Roxbury.
He will discuss anti-crime proposals to be included in his State of
the Union address. By Charles Radin and Ann Scales. 650 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LOTUS-PAPOWS (Orlando, Fla.) _ Jeff Papows, the embattled chief
executive of Lotus Development Corp., does his swan song at the
Lotusphere trade show, claiming to leave behind a company that has
met its financial targets and continues to extend its Notes and
Domino software to more users. By Hiawatha Bray. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   CYBER-MERGERS (Boston) _ GTE Corp.'s CyberTrust Solutions
division, which makes network security software, is snapped up for
$150 million by Baltimore Technologies Plc, Europe's largest maker
of software for encrypted communication and commerce. ScanSoft Inc.
agrees to buy California-based Caere Corp. for more than $140
million, combining their businesses in digital imaging software. By
Jerry Ackerman. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-JETS (Undated) -- NFL owners are expected to formally
approve Robert ``Woody'' Johnson as the new owner of the New York
Jets, a move that should expedite the Bill Belichick matter. By
Nick Cafardo. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-THRASHERS-BRUINS (Boston) _ Bruins, Thrashers battle to a
tie in a game in which star defenseman Ray Bourque is injured by a
slap shot. By Nancy Marrapese-Burrell. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-CELTICS-WIZARDS (Washington) _ Paul Pierce and Antoine
Walker power the Celtics to a win on the road. By Peter May. 800
words.
</P>
