<P>
   CLASSIC-BOOKS-EDUC (Chicago) _ A new program at Wilbur Wright
College, a community college on this city's North Side that caters
primarily to high school graduates considered not ready for
four-year institutions, allows students to earn a special minor or
certificate by taking a concentration of courses on the so-called
great books of the Western canon. What is different is that at
Wright and other institutions, most of them ranked in the middle to
lower end of the national academic pack, are taking steps to
underline such classes and to emphasize that they are critical to a
liberal arts education. By Jacques Steinberg. (The story has moved
