<P>
   SCI-INCOMPETENT-PEOPLE (Undated) _ A Cornell researcher has
found that most incompetent people do not know that they are
incompetent. People who do things badly, researchers found, are
usually supremely confident of their abilities _ more confident
than people who do things well. By Erica Goode. (The story has
moved in ``a'' news file.)
