<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-LIFESTYLE-MEDICINE-NYT, which
moved in ``a'' news file.) 
c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``It used to be when people who came out of school wanted to do
cosmetics, they were looked down on. At Harvard, they called it
`throwing the pearls to the swine.' Now, in terms of survival, it
is what you do.''
</P>
<P>
   _Dr. ALAN R. KLING, who practices cosmetic surgery in New York
City.
</P>
