<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CHOLA-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAMA CHOLA A ROLE MODEL FOR HERMOSILLO KIDS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 BY DENNIS WAGNER  
 c.2000 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
(PHOENIX) - Mama Chola watches proudly as a barrio teenager pounds
away at a punching bag.
</P>
<P>
   She teaches kids, the poorest of the poor, to fight.
</P>
<P>
   Against drugs.
</P>
<P>
   For themselves.
</P>
<P>
   Her real name is Francisca Gonzalez Gil, but everyone knows the
middle-age interloper by her gang nickname.
</P>
<P>
   She runs a school and boxing club for tough kids in Hermosillo,
Sonora's capital. And she fights for them, railing at a government
and culture that she believes have abandoned youth.
</P>
<P>
   Gonzalez Gil started this crusade six years ago, when her own
son slipped into gangs and narcotics. He is now studying to be a
lawyer.
</P>
<P>
   Her school is an abandoned mess next to a corner market.
Volunteers teach boxing to the young boys and stage occasional
tournaments on a rickety, wooden ring. Mama Chola teaches art in an
adjoining room - joyful, flowery pictures made from molded tin and
paint.
</P>
<P>
   There is another room, austere and small, for academic lessons.
</P>
<P>
   Gonzalez Gil claimed this corner of Hermosillo without right or
invitation; she just moved in and set up shop. She says neighbors
didn't welcome her or trust her. The local pushers spread rumors to
turn people against her. But, slowly, kids came around, and help
followed.
</P>
<P>
   Hermosillo's back streets offer few alternatives to vapors or
methamphetamine, which costs less than a meal.
</P>
<P>
   For Hermosillo's poor, the little cholos, as Gonzalez Gil calls
them, there are few resources, little help.
</P>
<P>
   The government? Gonzalez Gill shudders and quotes long-ago
Mexican President Benito Juarez: ``The law is for your enemies.''
It is an expression that both justifies and explains corruption.
</P>
<P>
   So she fights a lonely war, preaching against drugs that poison
people with greed, the drugs that spawn violence, destroy families
and breed crime. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-17-00 2235EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
